messages.content: What is the purpose of Fooocus_Nodes in ComfyUI?
Fooocus_Nodes is a set of custom nodes in ComfyUI that reproduces the same images generated from Fooocus in ComfyUI.
How can you install Fooocus_Nodes in ComfyUI?
To install Fooocus_Nodes in ComfyUI, you need to clone the repository `https://github.com/Seedsa/Fooocus_Nodes.git` to your ComfyUI `custom_nodes` directory.
How can you update Fooocus_Nodes in ComfyUI?
To update Fooocus_Nodes in ComfyUI, navigate to the cloned repo e.g. `custom_nodes/Fooocus_Nodes` and run `git pull`.
How can you enable model caching for improved model switch performance in Fooocus_Nodes?
To enable model caching for improved model switch performance in Fooocus_Nodes, open `/py/modules/config.py` and set `use_model_cache` to `True`.
What are some of the features available in Fooocus_Nodes?
Some of the features available in Fooocus_Nodes include Txt2image&Img2img, Inpaint&Outpaint, Upscale, ImagePrompt&FaceSwap, Canny&CPDS, Styles&PromptExpansion, DeftailerFix, and Describe.
Where can you find example workflows for Fooocus_Nodes?
Example workflows for Fooocus_Nodes can be found in the `./workflow/` directory.
What are the credits for Fooocus_Nodes?
The credits for Fooocus_Nodes include Fooocus, ComfyUI-Easy-Use, and ComfyUI.
